"Phillips L.F.","Surfing the nanowaves 2: Non-equilibrium thermodynamics of the gas-liquid interface",2010,"Chemical Physics Letters","495","1-3",,"1","7",,,10.1016/j.cplett.2010.06.013,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-77955556769&partnerID=40&md5=65b22d11e62ebc0182bb2ddceaad02b4","Chemistry Department, University of Canterbury, Christchurch, New Zealand","Phillips, L.F., Chemistry Department, University of Canterbury, Christchurch, New Zealand","The ultimate magnitude of global warming is likely to be limited mainly by the rate of absorption of CO2 by the oceans. Model calculations of this limit need to take account of the effect of the temperature gradient at the ocean surface on the effective saturation pressure of CO2 above that surface. We present a description of this and other unfamiliar phenomena in terms of Onsager's irreversible thermodynamics. © 2010 Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.",,"Effective saturation; Gas-liquid interface; Irreversible thermodynamics; Model calculations; Non equilibrium thermodynamics; Ocean surfaces; Onsager; Temperature gradient; Gas absorption; Global warming; Oceanography; Pressure effects; Thermodynamics; Phase interfaces",,,,,,"Denbigh, K.G., (1951) The Thermodynamics of the Steady State, , Methuen London; Denbigh, K.G., Raumann, G., (1952) Proc. Royal Soc. Lond. A, 210, p. 377; Denbigh, K.G., Raumann, G., (1952) Proc. Royal Soc. Lond. A, 210, p. 518; Spanner, D.C., (1954) Symp. Soc. Exp. Biol., 8, p. 76; Phillips, L.F., (2004) Accts. Chem. Res., 37, p. 982; Pao, Y.-P., (1971) Phys. Fluids (1958-1988), 14, p. 306; Fang, G., Ward, C.A., (1999) Phys. Rev. e, 59 (1 A), p. 417; Ward, C.A., Stanga, D., (2001) Phys. Rev. e, 64 (5 PART 1), p. 051509; Mills, C.T., Phillips, L.F., (2003) Chem. Phys. Lett., 372, p. 615; Leonard, D.I., Phillips, L.F., Rev. Sci. Instr., , in preparation; Pursell, C.J., Phillips, L.F., (2006) Phys. Chem. Chem. Phys., 8, p. 4694; Loyalka, S.K., Siewert, C.E., Thomas Jr., J.R., (1978) Ph